29/04/2011
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- A court in Bihac convicted two men Thursday (April 28th) of war crimes against civilians committed during the 1992-1995 Bosnian conflict. Lazar Ristic was sentenced to 20 years in prison while Predrag Devic got 12 years. They were found guilty of killing 15 Bosniak civilians in Sanski Most in 1995. (Onasa, BHRT, Radio Free Europe, Srna, Dnevni Avaz - 28/04/11)
